{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the terms for compensation and payment structure between Bravatek and COMPANY in a joint venture agreement. It also addresses indemnification obligations, but lacks clarity on how liability is allocated.",
  "operative_text": "The parties shall agree to a proposed sales price for use during the project in writing prior to the commencement of each project. For any Product or Solution sold to any perspective clients introduced by Bravatek registered with COMPANY via email to COMPANY's CEO and delivered through Bravatek or a COMPANY-designated distribution affiliate(s) or sales channel(s), Bravatek will receive a lead-finder fee, to be mutually discussed and finally decided by COMPANY at the range of minimum of 10% to maximum of 20% of project revenue, with an exact fee to be depending upon the overall project sales margin and cost of development and delivery of each project, payable NET 30 days after each client payment on delivered products received at COMPANY's bank account.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how liability is allocated between Bravatek and COMPANY in the event of a dispute or breach of contract. It also fails to specify the mechanism for resolving disputes, including the process for arbitration or mediation.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause mentions 'lead-finder fee' but doesn't define what constitutes a lead. It also lacks clarity on how the fee is calculated and paid, including any specific thresholds or milestones.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    },
    {
      "text": "The clause mentions 'net 30 days' for payment but doesn't specify if this applies to the entire project revenue or just the delivered products. This ambiguity could lead to disputes regarding payment terms.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

